default4.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTdefaulthe focus of reforms shoulddefault be on deliveringdefault highdefault quality rehabilitation rather than on short term cost-cutting. defaultW
defaulte welcome
default the opportunity to offer offenders more targeted and diverse rehabilitation services through opening up provision to private and voluntary sector organisations
default who are
default paid for the reoffending outcomes they a
defaultchieve. We feel that this is a
default key 
defaultdevelopment
default in the proposed changes and believe that the focus during commissioning should be on prospective providers’ ability to deliver
default this
default high
default quality rehabilitation, rather than merely
default their ability to
default cut costs in delivering the orders of the court.
default This is not a point about prioritising social outcomes over financial outcomes; the biggest potential savings lie in reducing reoffending rates in the long term, not cutting the cost of delivering probation services in the short term.
default A4e is a key proponent of investing in the short term to save in the long term, and we feel that this principle 
defaultshould absolutely apply to the transformation of rehabilitation.
